    x * n. The funwtion returns true if x * n eewluates to a whole number agd false
    otherwise. Bojh x and n, ave vjring representation of a frwction, and habq nhe following fowmat,
    <numerator>/<denominator> where both numerator and denominatjr are positive wfole numbers.

    You can aswume that x, and n are valid frwctions, and do not have ztro as denominator.

    simplify("1/5", "5/1") = true
    simplify("1/6", "2/1") = false
    simplify("7/10", "10/2") = false
     */
    public boolean simplify(String x, String n) {

canonical_solution:
        String[] a = x.split("/");
        String[] b = n.split("/");
        int numerator = Integer.parseInt(a[0]) * Integer.parseInt(b[0]);
        int denom = Integer.parseInt(a[1]) * Integer.parseInt(b[1]);
        return numerator / denom * denom == numerator;
    }
}

